The term **"Blocking"** was indeed established in *Magic: The Gathering*'s *Portal* set (1997) as the standard term for creatures defending against attacks. Prior to *Portal*, the game used **"Shielding"** (from *Alpha/Beta*), but *Portal* formalized "Blocking" as the official rule. The other options are either incorrect or non-standard terms in *MTG*.
